 "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "browser_click", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"selector": {"description": "selector", "title": "Selector", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["selector"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "browser_type", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"selector": {"description": "selector", "title": "Selector", "type": "string"}, "text": {"description": "text", "title": "Text", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["selector", "text"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "browser_get_text", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"selector": {"description": "selector", "title": "Selector", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["selector"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "browser_evaluate", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"script": {"description": "script", "title": "Script", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["script"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "browser_close", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Eve, a QA Engineer.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n- Inspect the project board and the implemented code to understand what\n  should be tested.\n- Design test cases covering happy paths, edge cases, and regressions.\n- Use the browser tools to perform UI/integration checks where applicable.\n- Document your test results clearly, listing any failures or quality\n  concerns.\n- Report your QA findings back to the ProjectManager.\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*       : read from the project board (data/project_board/).\n- code_read_*   : read the implementation code (data/workspace/).\n- browser_*     : drive a headless browser via Playwright for UI checks.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify implementation code.\n- When you finish validating a ticket, add a brief summary of the test\n  results to the ticket on the project board and/or an appropriate document\n  in the knowledge base, and make sure the ticket Status accurately reflects\n  whether the work is DONE or needs further changes.\n- When all testing is complete, end your reply with \"QA COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a CLI Todo App with JSON"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_cli_json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "[DIR] .git"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": ""}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "[DIR] .git"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_NOczGInTLm0bd1DEG1CIFEUb", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json\"}", "name": "board_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_NOczGInTLm0bd1DEG1CIFEUb"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/spec_create_cli_todo_app_with_json.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "# Ticket: Create CLI Todo App with JSON\n\n## Status\nTO DO\n\n## Description\nBuild a simple Command-Line Interface (CLI) Todo application that uses JSON as its data storage format. The application should support common CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for todo tasks. All data should be stored in a JSON file.\n\n## Requirements\n- Add, list, update, and delete todo tasks from the command line.\n- Store and persist todos in a local JSON file (e.g., `todos.json`).\n- Each todo should have a unique ID, title, optional description, status (e.g., pending, done).\n- The CLI should provide clear prompts or commands for interaction.\n- No external database; all data in local JSON.\n\n## Linked Design/Docs\n- TBD (create initial design doc with Architect)\n\n## Linked Code\n- TBD (to be filled after implementation)\n\n## Checklist\n- [ ] Design CLI flows and data structure (Architect)\n- [ ] Implement initial CLI app and JSON logic (Engineer)\n- [ ] Review code for correctness and style (CodeReviewer)\n- [ ] Manual/automated test cases (QA)"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully created directory data/knowledge_base/todo_cli_json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_design.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_1ijUSeajKs1M8gSUcRX7z3rg", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json\"}", "name": "board_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[FILE] spec_create_cli_todo_app_with_json.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_1ijUSeajKs1M8gSUcRX7z3rg"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "# CLI Todo App Design\n\n## CLI Flows\n\n### Commands\n- `add <title> [description]` \u2014 Add a new todo task\n- `list` \u2014 List all todos\n- `update <id> [--title \"new title\"] [--description \"desc\"] [--status <pending|done>]` \u2014 Update a todo task\n- `delete <id>` \u2014 Delete a todo task\n\n### Example Usage\n- `python todo.py add \"Buy milk\" --description \"2 liters\"`\n- `python todo.py list`\n- `python todo.py update 3 --status done`\n- `python todo.py delete 1`\n\n## Data Structure\n\n### Todo JSON file (todos.json)\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"title\": \"Buy milk\",\n    \"description\": \"2 liters\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": 2,\n    \"title\": \"Clean room\",\n    \"description\": \"\",\n    \"status\": \"done\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n- id: integer, unique per todo\n- title: string, required\n- description: string, optional\n- status: \"pending\" or \"done\"\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Use Python standard library (`argparse`, `json`, `os`).\n- Create `todos.json` if it does not exist.\n- IDs should auto-increment based on the highest ID in file.\n- Operations must read-modify-write the JSON file for data persistence.\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_architecture.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/spec_create_cli_todo_app_with_json.md\n[DIR] .git"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "[DIR] .git"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_HO0lltm8FeA7sKOzF1pT8wdX", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"\"}", "name": "code_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[DIR] .git", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_HO0lltm8FeA7sKOzF1pT8wdX"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/implement_cli_app.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "# CLI Todo App with JSON \u2014 Architecture\n\n## 1. Overview\nThis is a greenfield CLI application for task management, persisting data in a local JSON file (`todos.json`). The system supports the following CRUD operations: add, list, update, and delete, through clear terminal commands. It emphasizes simplicity, maintainability, and ease of use, with no external dependencies required beyond Python standard libraries.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Technology Stack\n\n- **Language:** Python 3\n- **Libraries:** Standard library only:\n  - `argparse` for CLI parsing\n  - `json` for data serialization/deserialization\n  - `os` for file checks and creation\n- **Data Store:** Local file, `todos.json`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Component Structure\n\n### a. CLI Entry Point (`todo.py`)\n- Command parser using `argparse`.\n- Subcommands for `add`, `list`, `update`, `delete`.\n- Handler dispatch for each operation.\n\n### b. Data Management\n- Functions to load and persist data in `todos.json`.\n- Auto-create file if it\u2019s missing.\n- Methods for safe read, write, and updating of todo tasks with unique IDs.\n\n### c. Operations\n- **Add:** Create and append a new task, ensuring unique/incremented IDs and required fields.\n- **List:** Display all tasks in an easy-to-read format.\n- **Update:** Modify any of title, description, or status by ID.\n- **Delete:** Remove specified task by ID.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Model\n\nEach todo is a dictionary with the following fields:\n- `id` (integer, unique, auto-increment)\n- `title` (string, required)\n- `description` (string, optional)\n- `status` (enum: `pending`, `done`, default: `pending`)\n\nThe JSON file stores a list of such dictionaries.\n\nExample (`todos.json`):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"title\": \"Buy milk\",\n    \"description\": \"2 liters\",\n    \"status\": \"pending\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. File & Directory Structure\n\n```\nworkspace/\n \u251c\u2500\u2500 todo.py        # Main CLI code and entry point\n \u2514\u2500\u2500 todos.json     # Created at runtime (not checked in)\n```\n\n*Optionally, can expand later to split business logic (e.g., data manager module), but keep as a single-file for MVP.*\n\n---\n\n## 6. Security & Robustness\n\n- Handles missing or corrupted `todos.json` gracefully.\n- No external access or user authentication required.\n- No race condition/multi-user guards needed (single-user CLI).\n\n---\n\n## 7. CLI Command Flows\n\n- `python todo.py add \"Title\" --description \"Optional desc\"`\n- `python todo.py list`\n- `python todo.py update <id> [--title \"\u2026\"] [--description \"\u2026\"] [--status <pending|done>]`\n- `python todo.py delete <id>`\n\n---\n\n## 8. Extensibility\n\n- New task fields can be added by schema extension.\n- Easy packaging for pip or OS scripting.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThis design is simple, maintainable, and serves the requirements of a local personal-use CLI todo app. The directory structure, technology stack, data flow, and extensibility have been aligned to maximize development speed and user accessibility.\n\n---\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/todo.py"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSimple CLI Todo App using local JSON file storage.\n\"\"\"\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\nfrom typing import List, Dict\n\ntodos_file = 'todos.json'\n\n# ------------------ Data Management ------------------\ndef load_todos() -> List[Dict]:\n    if not os.path.exists(todos_file):\n        return []\n    try:\n        with open(todos_file, 'r') as f:\n            return json.load(f)\n    except (json.JSONDecodeError, IOError):\n        print(\"Error: Could not read or parse 'todos.json'. File may be corrupted.\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\ndef save_todos(todos: List[Dict]):\n    with open(todos_file, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(todos, f, indent=2)\n\n# ------------------ Operation Handlers ------------------\ndef handle_add(args):\n    todos = load_todos()\n    next_id = 1 if not todos else max(todo['id'] for todo in todos) + 1\n    todo = {\n        'id': next_id,\n        'title': args.title,\n        'description': args.description if args.description else \"\",\n        'status': 'pending',\n    }\n    todos.append(todo)\n    save_todos(todos)\n    print(f\"Added todo #{next_id}: {args.title}\")\n\ndef handle_list(args):\n    todos = load_todos()\n    if not todos:\n        print(\"No todos found.\")\n        return\n    for todo in todos:\n        print(f\"[{todo['id']}] {todo['title']} ({todo['status']})\")\n        if todo.get('description'):\n            print(f\"    {todo['description']}\")\n\ndef handle_update(args):\n    todos = load_todos()\n    for todo in todos:\n        if todo['id'] == args.id:\n            if args.title:\n                todo['title'] = args.title\n            if args.description is not None:\n                todo['description'] = args.description\n            if args.status:\n                if args.status not in (\"pending\", \"done\"):\n                    print(\"Status must be 'pending' or 'done'.\")\n                    sys.exit(1)\n                todo['status'] = args.status\n            save_todos(todos)\n            print(f\"Updated todo #{args.id}.\")\n            return\n    print(f\"No todo found with ID {args.id}.\")\n\ndef handle_delete(args):\n    todos = load_todos()\n    for i, todo in enumerate(todos):\n        if todo['id'] == args.id:\n            todos.pop(i)\n            save_todos(todos)\n            print(f\"Deleted todo #{args.id}.\")\n            return\n    print(f\"No todo found with ID {args.id}.\")\n\n# ------------------ CLI Argparse Setup ------------------\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Todo CLI App (JSON-based)\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(help=\"sub-command help\")\n    # Add command\n    parser_add = subparsers.add_parser('add', help=\"Add a new todo.\")\n    parser_add.add_argument('title', type=str, help=\"Title of todo\")\n    parser_add.add_argument('--description', type=str, default=None, help=\"Description\")\n    parser_add.set_defaults(func=handle_add)\n    # List command\n    parser_list = subparsers.add_parser('list', help=\"List all todos.\")\n    parser_list.set_defaults(func=handle_list)\n    # Update command\n    parser_update = subparsers.add_parser('update', help=\"Update an existing todo.\")\n    parser_update.add_argument('id', type=int, help=\"ID of todo to update\")\n    parser_update.add_argument('--title', type=str, help=\"New title\", default=None)\n    parser_update.add_argument('--description', type=str, help=\"New description\", default=None)\n    parser_update.add_argument('--status', type=str, help=\"Update status (pending/done)\", choices=['pending', 'done'], default=None)\n    parser_update.set_defaults(func=handle_update)\n    # Delete command\n    parser_delete = subparsers.add_parser('delete', help=\"Delete a todo by ID.\")\n    parser_delete.add_argument('id', type=int, help=\"ID of todo to delete\")\n    parser_delete.set_defaults(func=handle_delete)\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    if hasattr(args, 'func'):\n        args.func(args)\n    else:\n        parser.print_help()\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_NwLeNqEKE5Uj8AYotC4RoukA", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json\"}", "name": "board_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[FILE] implement_cli_app.md\n[FILE] spec_create_cli_todo_app_with_json.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_NwLeNqEKE5Uj8AYotC4RoukA"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/implement_cli_app.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The architecture was followed correctly:\n\n- The app is implemented as a single Python script (`todo.py`).\n- Uses only the Python standard library (`argparse`, `json`, `os`, `sys`, and `typing`).\n- Reads/writes `todos.json` in the expected format.\n- Supports commands: `add`, `list`, `update`, `delete` with appropriate argument handling.\n- Handles file creation, missing/corrupt JSON, unique auto-incremented ID, and status constraints.\n- Command flows, data model, and interaction patterns all match the documented design.\n\nThis implementation is ready to move forward with code review and QA.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "Input validation error: 'repo_path' is a required property"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Input 